<item>
            <title>[ZOOKEEPER-137] client watcher objects can lose events</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-137</link>
                <project id="12310801" key="ZOOKEEPER">ZooKeeper</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;if a single watcher (A) is registered on a single node for both a getdata and exists watch the second watch event may be lost:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) getdata(&quot;node&quot;, A)&lt;br/&gt;
2) setdata(&quot;node&quot;...)&lt;br/&gt;
3) exists(&quot;node&quot;, A)&lt;br/&gt;
4) delete(&quot;node&quot;...)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if watch events for 2 is processed on the client (zookeeper.java, zkwatcher) after 3 completes then the zkwatcher process event method will clear the watch and the subsequent operation&apos;s (4) event will be ignored&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
